Dear Hiring Team, 

It is with great pleasure that I submit my candidacy for the Rust Software Engineer position with Spice AI. I bring over three years of professional experience in distributed systems, database internals, and AI infrastructure, along with a strong academic foundation as a Master of Science in Computer Science graduate from Pace University, NY.

Through my experience across two engineering roles, I have built and delivered production-grade systems that directly reflect the high-performance database and distributed systems expertise this position demands. As a Software Engineer at Sperse, I architected a high-performance AI interaction layer translating natural-language intents into safe, validated tool calls across 1,000+ distributed endpoints — requiring rigorous API contract design, distributed coordination, and production-grade reliability. I optimized query routing and query federation to maximize KV-cache hit rates, reducing latency by 60% and LLM API costs by 50% through targeted performance profiling and system-level optimizations — the kind of database-level performance work central to Spice.ai's mission. To keep these systems production-ready, I designed an observability layer using Langfuse and LangSmith for distributed tracing, structured logs, and evaluation hooks, giving me hands-on experience with the operational rigor required for enterprise-grade data infrastructure. Prior to Sperse, as a Software Engineer at Qualitest, I designed a cloud-agnostic Storage Service using Python, PostgreSQL, and Redis that handled file operations across AWS S3, Google Cloud Storage, and MinIO — giving me direct experience with cloud-native development, distributed systems design, and multi-environment data access patterns. I also developed backend workflows using AWS Step Functions for long-running data import jobs, ensuring fault-tolerant distributed processing at scale. Together, these roles have prepared me to design and build high-performance database engine features and contribute meaningfully to Spice.ai OSS and the Spice.ai Cloud Platform.

My academic research experience has given me a rigorous foundation in high-performance computing, GPU-accelerated systems, and open source collaboration — skills that translate directly into the technical depth and open source culture this role values. As an AI Researcher at the Pace Artificial Intelligence Lab, I conducted research on StyleGAN and Stable Diffusion using CUDA, PyTorch, and LoRA on Pace University's HPC cluster for distributed model training and fine-tuning. I architected a model inference pipeline with vLLM for high-performance serving and Hugging Face deployment, ensuring production-ready model serving with optimized throughput — experience that aligns with Spice.ai's focus on fast, reliable infrastructure for AI applications. Beyond my professional work, I maintain Dark Factory, an open source orchestrator for AI coding CLIs built with Rust (Crossterm, Ratatui, Y-crdt), demonstrating systems-level programming and distributed coordination using CRDTs to signal orchestrator state across machines. This project reflects my commitment to open source development and my ability to design fault-tolerant, distributed systems — core values at Spice AI.

I have always been passionate about simplifying AI application development for all developers and unifying data infrastructure into accessible, high-performance runtimes, and I envision myself contributing my talent to the furthering of Spice AI's mission to make building AI-powered software as easy as building a modern web application. I would love to discuss my interest in this position with your team and can be reached at #ph or #eml. Thank you for your time and consideration, I look forward to connecting!

